name: cantools
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "cantools" %}
{% set version = "20.6.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "1cc876ec1c8de17bafc6f631292d9d71902da06aae6a394ec6fc3f4f5518389f" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv "
  entry_points:
    - cantools=cantools.__init__:_main

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - pip
    - bitstruct>=3.7.0
    - pyparsing>=2.0.3
    - python-can>=2.1.0
  run:
    - python
    - bitstruct>=3.7.0
    - pyparsing>=2.0.3
    - python-can>=2.1.0

test:
  imports:
    - cantools

about:
  home: https://github.com/eerimoq/cantools
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'CAN BUS tools.'
  description: |
    CAN BUS tools
    - `DBC`_, `KCD`_ and SYM file parsing.
    - CAN message encoding and decoding.
    - Simple and extended signal multiplexing.
    - ``candump`` output decoder.
    - Node `tester`_.
  doc_url: http://cantools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/eerimoq/cantools

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - danielhrisca
